Usage: releasify publish [--path|-p <path>] [--semver|-s <relese>] [--tag|-t <pattern>] [--verbose|-v <level>] [--help|-h]
  publish to npm a new version of a module and create the GitHub Release with the changelogs

  -p, --path <path>
      The path to the project to release. Default `pwd`

  -t, --tag <pattern>
      The pattern of the tag to release. Useful for multi-branch project. Default `v${major version of the project}.\d+.\d+`

  -s, --semver <release>
      Force the release type. The value must be [major, premajor, minor, preminor, patch, prepatch, prerelease]

  -v, --verbose <level>
      Print out more info. The value must be [debug, info, warn, error]

  -h, --help
      Show this help message


'remote',
'branch',
'npm-access',
'npm-tag',
'gh-token',
'gh-release-draft',
'gh-release-prerelease'],

